rows.NAME: Root Page
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Alias of the root UI page of the app

rows.NAME: App ID
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Unique identifier of the app, which must correspond to the component name

rows.NAME: Title
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: The entry is language-dependent and specified via {{…}} syntax

rows.NAME: Subtitle
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Language-dependent entry for a subtitle; specified via {{...}} syntax

rows.NAME: Short Title
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Short version of the title. Language-dependent entry has to be specified via {{...}} syntax

rows.NAME: CDM-Info
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Needed for CDM (Common Data Model) conversion of tiles. Language-dependent entry has to be specified via {{...}} syntax

rows.NAME: Description
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Language-dependent entry that is specified via {{…}} syntax

rows.NAME: Project Name
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Language-independent project name

rows.NAME: UI5 Source URI
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: URI of the UI5 sources relative to app root (index.html) or absolute

rows.NAME: UI5 Theme
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Theme to use in the exported app: e.g. sap_belize

rows.NAME: UI5 App Control
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Qualified name of the app control to be used: e.g. sap.m.App

rows.NAME: Root URL
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Path to the folder containing the app's index.html relative to server root

rows.NAME: Progressive Web App
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Check to make the exported app progressive allowing it to work offline. This will add PWA-specific properties to the manifest.json

rows.NAME: Export Folder
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Path to the export folder - absolute or relative to the installation root folder. The path may contain placeholders with column names from the input data sheet.

rows.NAME: OData $batch for writes
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Check to bundle multiple POST/PUT/PATCH requests in a $batch request, thus placing them in a single transaction.

rows.NAME: OData $batch for deletes
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Check to bundle multiple DELETE requests in a $batch request, thus placing them in a single transaction.

rows.NAME: OData $batch for FunctionImports
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Check to bundle multiple requests for OData FunctionImports in a $batch request, thus placing them in a single transaction.

rows.NAME: Relative URLs in OData
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If not set, data sources in the manifest.json will have the absolute URLs used in the workbench's connections. In most cases, it is better to have relative URLs, so the exported apps can be deployed on different NetWeaver instances.

rows.NAME: Export credentials to manifest.json
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If checked, data connection credentials (username, password, etc.) will be exported to the default connection in manifest.json.

rows.NAME: Export SAP client to manifest.json
rows.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: If checked, the data connection's sap-client will be exported to the default connection in manifest.json.
